Overcome is the fourth studio album by metalcore band, All That Remains. It 
was released on September 16, 2008.

On July 21, 2008, two tracks from the new album - Before the Damned and 
Relinquish - made their debut on the band&#039;s MySpace profile. Commenting on 
the tracks, vocalist Philip Labonte stated, "This represents the heavier side of 
ATR. Last time we did this we put up &#039;The Weak Willed&#039; and we feel like it&#039;s a 
bit of a tradition to really kick you in the nuts when we first show off new 
stuff! So here is the heaviest stuff we came up with for &#039;Overcome.&#039;" Chiron 
made its debut on August 11, 2008 on the band&#039;s MySpace. The song is the 
first single from the album, with a behind-the-scenes shoot up and the official 
music video up on YouTube.

Two of the album&#039;s tracks, "Two Weeks," and "Chiron," were made available 
as downloadable content for Rock Band on September 9, 2008. The tracks 
are exclusive to Rock Band for one week before the album is released.

The song "Two Weeks" was added to the band&#039;s MySpace page on 
September 08, 2008 to help promote the release of the song pack on Rock 
Band. It will be the album&#039;s second single with a video being filmed for it.
